         <entryFree xml:id="k000125" type="architectural feature">
            <term xml:id="term-k000125-4" xml:lang="zh-latn-pinyin-nt" source="#biblk000125-1"
               >wudian</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000125-1" xml:lang="zh-Hant">廡殿</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000125-2" xml:lang="zh-Hans">庑殿</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000125-3" xml:lang="zh-latn-pinyin" source="#biblk000125-2"
               >wǔdiàn</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000125-5" xml:lang="zh-latn-wadegile">wu-tien</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000125-6" xml:lang="en" source="#biblk000125-3">hip roof</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000125-7" xml:lang="en" source="#biblk000125-4">hipped roof</term>
            <note type="Note (brief)">
               <p xml:lang="en" source="#biblk000125-1"> Wudianding 廡殿頂 (also 廡殿), literally the
                  roof of an audience hall (Kroll usually translated as a “hip roof,” is a type of
                  roof which consists of a central ridge, four sloped ridges, and four sloped
                  surfaces, which are typically covered in ceramic roof tiles. This form of roof was
                  mostly used for palace or other large-scale buildings. The term wudian is first
                  seen in documents of the Qing Dynasty. In the Tang and Song Dynasties, this roof
                  type was called si`e 四阿. According Yingzaofashi 營造法式, ”si`e palatial halls”（si’e
                  diange 四阿殿閣）can also be called "five-ridge halls" (wujidian 五脊殿) as well as Wudian
                  吳殿). The Yingzao fayuan 營造法原, which discusses the architectural practices of the
                  Jiangnan region during the Yuan and Ming Dynasties, used the term "si heshe” 四合舍
                  for this kind of roof (Yao Chengzu, Zhang Zhigang, Liu Dunzhen 1986: 37). </p>
               <p xml:lang="zh-Hant" source="#biblk000125-2"> "
                  “廡殿”，是中国古代建筑的一种屋顶形式，指具有一道正脊、四条垂脊、四面坡的屋頂。从唐宋以来的文献资料看，这种屋顶形式多用于宫殿建筑或规模较大的大式建筑。（唐《營繕令》：“宮殿皆四阿，施鴟尾。”（[日]狩谷益斎
                  校订，明治16年（1883年）刊，卷三《（第六）居處部·居宅類·鴟尾》：2b）[NoSource]
                  庑殿一词用于指这种屋顶形式的用法最早出现於清代，（[清]佚名，帝闕城垣規制（不分卷），清內府鈔本）[zotero K7QW8S3C] [清]工部，清雍正十二年（1773）刻本，目录和卷一）[zotero T5QHEK76]
                  唐宋时期这种屋顶形式被称为“四阿”，宋《营造法式》中又称“四阿殿阁”为“五脊殿”、“吳殿”。（法式卷五) [zotero CT4CSDB8 ]
                  反应了元明以来江南地区建筑做法的《营造法原》[zotero UWHU6CTI] 中称这种屋顶形式为“四合舍”。（姚承祖，张志刚，刘敦桢，1986：37） （Jia
                  Tingli賈亭立， Ma Jiaqi 馬嘉琪）"</p>
            </note>
